main event: Five unidentified objects were observed over Neah Bay, Washington for over 2 hours on September 20, 1954.
interesting points: The objects were described as two round, small, red and green objects that were flashing red, white, and green while moving very slowly.
No visual intercept was attempted, and the objects were not visually made by two aircraft.
The objects were larger than a large commercial airliner.
Visual contact was made with the objects from Hamilton Air Force Base in California.
The objects were reported to be circular and dull red in color.
